spotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5184x3456+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5b%2Fdd%2F6dba39f2448bbef4fa026d9b6089%2Fimg-6194.JPG 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5184x3456+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5b%2Fdd%2F6dba39f2448bbef4fa026d9b6089%2Fimg-6194.JPG 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5184x3456+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5b%2Fdd%2F6dba39f2448bbef4fa026d9b6089%2Fimg-6194.JPG 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5184x3456+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5b%2Fdd%2F6dba39f2448bbef4fa026d9b6089%2Fimg-6194.JPG 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5184x3456+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5b%2Fdd%2F6dba39f2448bbef4fa026d9b6089%2Fimg-6194.JPG 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5184x3456+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5b%2Fdd%2F6dba39f2448bbef4fa026d9b6089%2Fimg-6194.JPG 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5184x3456+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5b%2Fdd%2F6dba39f2448bbef4fa026d9b6089%2Fimg-6194.JPG 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5184x3456+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5b%2Fdd%2F6dba39f2448bbef4fa026d9b6089%2Fimg-6194.JPG" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5184x3456+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5b%2Fdd%2F6dba39f2448bbef4fa026d9b6089%2Fimg-6194.JPG" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5184x3456+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5b%2Fdd%2F6dba39f2448bbef4fa026d9b6089%2Fimg-6194.JPG" class="img" alt="Chelsea Tan and her friends participate in a &amp;quot;prosperity toss&amp;quot; for the Lunar New Year." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Chelsea Tan and her friends participate in a "prosperity toss" for the Lunar New Year.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Courtesy Chelsea Tan                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Teo, who calls this dish &lt;em&gt;lo hei, &lt;/em&gt;says &lt;em&gt;lo &lt;/em&gt;means to mix but can also mean the act of doing business. "So tossing the salad higher means your business or work will improve next year. Hei means happiness."&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Mary Yee fondly remembers her mother and aunts making dumplings on the Lunar New Year as the family gathered for a large meal. Although my grandparents and parents are no longer with us, I am grateful for their sharing these traditions with me so that I may pass them along to my children, grandchildren, and the generations to come," she said.&lt;/p&gt;       &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Dress for success&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-44566" class="bucketwrap image medium"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 3580;         --source-height: 5370;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3580x5370+0+0/resize/200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb6%2F10%2Ffd5164394bbb84d22c846802c3a9%2Fdsc05139.jpeg 200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3580x5370+0+0/resize/300/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb6%2F10%2Ffd5164394bbb84d22c846802c3a9%2Fdsc05139.jpeg 300w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3580x5370+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb6%2F10%2Ffd5164394bbb84d22c846802c3a9%2Fdsc05139.jpeg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3580x5370+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb6%2F10%2Ffd5164394bbb84d22c846802c3a9%2Fdsc05139.jpeg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3580x5370+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb6%2F10%2Ffd5164394bbb84d22c846802c3a9%2Fdsc05139.jpeg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3580x5370+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb6%2F10%2Ffd5164394bbb84d22c846802c3a9%2Fdsc05139.jpeg 1600w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3580x5370+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb6%2F10%2Ffd5164394bbb84d22c846802c3a9%2Fdsc05139.jpeg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 300px, (min-width: 1025px) 300px, (min-width: 768px) 252px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3580x5370+0+0/resize/200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb6%2F10%2Ffd5164394bbb84d22c846802c3a9%2Fdsc05139.jpeg 200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3580x5370+0+0/resize/300/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb6%2F10%2Ffd5164394bbb84d22c846802c3a9%2Fdsc05139.jpeg 300w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3580x5370+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb6%2F10%2Ffd5164394bbb84d22c846802c3a9%2Fdsc05139.jpeg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3580x5370+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb6%2F10%2Ffd5164394bbb84d22c846802c3a9%2Fdsc05139.jpeg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3580x5370+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb6%2F10%2Ffd5164394bbb84d22c846802c3a9%2Fdsc05139.jpeg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3580x5370+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb6%2F10%2Ffd5164394bbb84d22c846802c3a9%2Fdsc05139.jpeg 1600w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3580x5370+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb6%2F10%2Ffd5164394bbb84d22c846802c3a9%2Fdsc05139.jpeg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 300px, (min-width: 1025px) 300px, (min-width: 768px) 252px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3580x5370+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb6%2F10%2Ffd5164394bbb84d22c846802c3a9%2Fdsc05139.jpeg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3580x5370+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fb6%2F10%2Ffd5164394bbb84d22c846802c3a9%2Fdsc05139.jpeg" class="img" alt="Kristen Morita dresses her and her daughter up in traditional and modern Chinese cheongsam." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Kristen Morita dresses her and her daughter up in traditional and modern Chinese cheongsam.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Courtesty Kristin Morita                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Many readers look forward to wearing a new outfit to symbolize a fresh start. Others like to wear clothing that is traditional to their cultures, like food blogger Kristen Morita, who wears a traditional Chinese cheongsam for the holiday. She says she wore her mother's cheongsam to her wedding and later learned that more modern interpretations of the dress are available. Now, she and her children celebrate their traditions through fashion.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Lena Chen of Sebastopol, Calif., did not grow up with a lot of money. She remembers when her mother saved all year to buy fabrics to make new clothes for her as a child. "It was the most beautiful red dress my sister and I had ever worn! After all these years, I still remember it as a labor of love from my mother."&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;In addition to the clothes, some believe your hair can determine your luck for the year. Karen Yee of San Francisco, says she doesn't cut or wash her hair on New Year's Day. "Hair and luck in Chinese are homonyms," she said. "So if you cut or wash your hair on the day of the Lunar New Year, it means you are washing or cutting the luck you have at the start of the year."&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-44569" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 640;         --source-height: 480;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/640x480+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5f%2F4f%2F52b0e6a24b43a812d035266ed225%2Fimg-8388.jpeg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/640x480+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5f%2F4f%2F52b0e6a24b43a812d035266ed225%2Fimg-8388.jpeg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/640x480+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5f%2F4f%2F52b0e6a24b43a812d035266ed225%2Fimg-8388.jpeg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/640x480+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5f%2F4f%2F52b0e6a24b43a812d035266ed225%2Fimg-8388.jpeg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/640x480+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5f%2F4f%2F52b0e6a24b43a812d035266ed225%2Fimg-8388.jpeg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/640x480+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5f%2F4f%2F52b0e6a24b43a812d035266ed225%2Fimg-8388.jpeg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/640x480+0+