63x2004+0+372/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd3%2F64%2Fc3cfc1b04959b0a213ee22f6ae93%2Fgettyimages-2194544932.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3563x2004+0+372/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fd3%2F64%2Fc3cfc1b04959b0a213ee22f6ae93%2Fgettyimages-2194544932.jpg" class="img" alt="Snow falls on Chartres Street in the French Quarter on Jan. 21, in New Orleans, La." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Snow falls on Chartres Street in the French Quarter on Jan. 21, in New Orleans, La.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Michael DeMocker/Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A rare winter storm has impacted the U.S. Gulf Coast, bringing heavy snow, sleet and ice that have made travel conditions dangerous.&lt;/strong&gt; Governors in Louisiana, Mississippi, Alabama, Georgia and Florida have declared states of emergency. Officials throughout the region are urging residents to stay in place and prepare for potential power outages. Forecasters are predicting historic amounts of snowfall in many areas. Check out the &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/the-picture-show/2025/01/21/g-s1-44004/photos-texas-florida-rare-winter-storm-historic-snowfall" target="_blank"&gt;snow photos from Texas to Florida&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Life advice&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="res1134223482" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 4490;         --source-height: 2525;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2022/11/03/gettyimages-1359131145_wide-fdc276eb92ba0ae896d8eec31b4a15080e5ffadc.jpg?s=400&amp;c=85&amp;f=webp 400w, https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2022/11/03/gettyimages-1359131145_wide-fdc276eb92ba0ae896d8eec31b4a15080e5ffadc.jpg?s=600&amp;c=85&amp;f=webp 600w, https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2022/11/03/gettyimages-1359131145_wide-fdc276eb92ba0ae896d8eec31b4a15080e5ffadc.jpg?s=800&amp;c=85&amp;f=webp 800w, https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2022/11/03/gettyimages-1359131145_wide-fdc276eb92ba0ae896d8eec31b4a15080e5ffadc.jpg?s=900&amp;c=85&amp;f=webp 900w, https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2022/11/03/gettyimages-1359131145_wide-fdc276eb92ba0ae896d8eec31b4a15080e5ffadc.jpg?s=1200&amp;c=85&amp;f=webp 1200w, https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2022/11/03/gettyimages-1359131145_wide-fdc276eb92ba0ae896d8eec31b4a15080e5ffadc.jpg?s=1600&amp;c=85&amp;f=webp 1600w, https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2022/11/03/gettyimages-1359131145_wide-fdc276eb92ba0ae896d8eec31b4a15080e5ffadc.jpg?s=1800&amp;c=85&amp;f=webp 1800w" data-template="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2022/11/03/gettyimages-1359131145_wide-fdc276eb92ba0ae896d8eec31b4a15080e5ffadc.jpg?s={width}&amp;c={quality}&amp;f={format}" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2022/11/03/gettyimages-1359131145_wide-fdc276eb92ba0ae896d8eec31b4a15080e5ffadc.jpg?s=400&amp;c=85&amp;f=jpeg 400w, https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2022/11/03/gettyimages-1359131145_wide-fdc276eb92ba0ae896d8eec31b4a15080e5ffadc.jpg?s=600&amp;c=85&amp;f=jpeg 600w, https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2022/11/03/gettyimages-1359131145_wide-fdc276eb92ba0ae896d8eec31b4a15080e5ffadc.jpg?s=800&amp;c=85&amp;f=jpeg 800w, https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2022/11/03/gettyimages-1359131145_wide-fdc276eb92ba0ae896d8eec31b4a15080e5ffadc.jpg?s=900&amp;c=85&amp;f=jpeg 900w, https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2022/11/03/gettyimages-1359131145_wide-fdc276eb92ba0ae896d8eec31b4a15080e5ffadc.jpg?s=1200&amp;c=85&amp;f=jpeg 1200w, https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2022/11/03/gettyimages-1359131145_wide-fdc276eb92ba0ae896d8eec31b4a15080e5ffadc.jpg?s=1600&amp;c=85&amp;f=jpeg 1600w, https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2022/11/03/gettyimages-1359131145_wide-fdc276eb92ba0ae896d8eec31b4a15080e5ffadc.jpg?s=1800&amp;c=85&amp;f=jpeg 1800w" data-template="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2022/11/03/gettyimages-1359131145_wide-fdc276eb92ba0ae896d8eec31b4a15080e5ffadc.jpg?s={width}&amp;c={quality}&amp;f={format}" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2022/11/03/gettyimages-1359131145_wide-fdc276eb92ba0ae896d8eec31b4a15080e5ffadc.jpg?s=1100&amp;c=50&amp;f=jpeg" data-template="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2022/11/03/gettyimages-1359131145_wide-fdc276eb92ba0ae896d8eec31b4a15080e5ffadc.jpg?s={width}&amp;c={quality}&amp;f={format}" class="img" alt="Conceptual image of woman managing her spending. She holds a purple credit card in her hand and different objects float around it, a piggy bank, a shopping card, a car, a plate of food and a house." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt;          &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;      &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Credit card reward programs can bring big perks like hotel and air travel upgrades. &lt;/strong&gt;You can even get cash back for gas and groceries. Finance journalist Katherine Fan got into credit card points after college and has reaped the benefits. Fan explains how to choose the right card and &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2022/11/03/1134223194/how-to-get-into-credit-card-points-for-beginners" target="_blank"&gt;what to know before signing up&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;💳 &lt;strong&gt;If you are looking for a premium card&lt;/strong&gt;, your credit score should be closer to 720. Those cards offer bigger rewards.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;💳 &lt;strong&gt;Get a card that makes sense for your spending habits.&lt;/strong&gt; If you travel, look for a card that offers perks that help with those needs.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;💳 &lt;strong&gt;If you are hesitant about paying an annual fee&lt;/strong&gt;, consider cards that don't have one.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;💳 &lt;strong&gt;Points can feel like free money&lt;/strong&gt;, but you should plan your spending around what makes economic sense for your life. Consider whether the money you are spending is worth it or if you are spending money just to earn points.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;       &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;3 things to know before you go&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-43985" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 6000;         --source-height: 3375;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F92%2F00%2F4ee7cf5648c39ad3a8d4d2ede174%2Fprinceharry-dealbook.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F92%2F00%2F4ee7cf5648c39ad3a8d4d2ede174%2Fprinceharry-dealbook.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F92%2F00%2F4ee7cf5648c39ad3a8d4d2ede174%2Fprinceharry-dealbook.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F92%2F00%2F4ee7cf5648c39ad3a8d4d2ede174%2Fprinceharry-dealbook.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F92%2F00%2F4ee7cf5648c39ad3a8d4d2ede174%2Fprinceharry-dealbook.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F92%2F00%2F4ee7cf5648c39ad3a8d4d2ede174%2Fprinceharry-dealbook.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F92%2F00%2F4ee7cf5648c39ad3a8d4d2ede174%2Fprinceharry-dealbook.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F92%2F00%2F4ee7cf5648c39ad3a8d4d2ede174%2Fprinceharry-dealbook.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F92%2F00%2F4ee7cf5648c39ad3a8d4d2ede174%2Fprinceharry-dealbook.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F92%2F00%2F4ee7cf5648c39ad3a8d4d2ede174%2Fprinceharry-dealbook.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F92%2F00%2F4ee7cf5648c39ad3a8d4d2ede174%2Fprinceharry-dealbook.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F92%2F00%2F4ee7cf5648c39ad3a8d4d2ede174%2Fprinceharry-dealbook.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F92%2F00%2F4ee7cf5648c39ad3a8d4d2ede174%2Fprinceharry-dealbook.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F92%2F00%2F4ee7cf5648c39ad3a8d4d2ede174%2Fprinceharry-dealbook.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F92%2F00%2F4ee7cf5648c39ad3a8d4d2ede174%2Fprinceharry-dealbook.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F92%2F00%2F4ee7cf5648c39ad3a8d4d2ede174%2Fprinceharry-dealbook.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F92%2F00%2F4ee7cf5648c39ad3a8d4d2ede174%2Fprinceharry-dealbook.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F92%2F00%2F4ee7cf5648c39ad3a8d4d2ede174%2Fprinceharry-dealbook.jpg" class="img" alt="Prince Harry said his lawsuit against Rupert Murdoch&amp;#039;s British tabloids was about holding the media accountable, during the New York Times DealBook summit in December." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Prince Harry said his lawsuit against Rupert Murdoch's British tabloids was about holding the media accountable, during the &lt;em&gt;New York Times&lt;/em&gt; DealBook summit in December.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Michael M. Santiago/Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Prince Harry and a British lawmaker have agreed to settle with Rupert Murdoch's British publishing arm.&lt;/strong&gt; The deal ends years of struggle to &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/01/22/nx-s1-5269980/trial-prince-harry-rupert-murdoch-tabloids" target="_blank"&gt;hold the tabloids accountable for illegal privacy invasions&lt;/a&gt; and alleged cover-up of crimes.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The FDA has expanded its approval of Spravato&lt;/strong&gt;, an antidepressant nasal spray, to now be used as &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/shots-health-news/2025/01/21/nx-s1-5269780/fda-allows-standalone-use-of-nasal-spray-antidepressant-spravato-esketamine" target="_blank"&gt;a standalone treatment for depression&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pulitzer Prize-winning cartoonist and playwright Jules Feiffer&lt;/strong&gt;, known for illustrating the children's classic &lt;em&gt;The Phantom Tollbooth&lt;/em&gt;, &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/01/21/839273361/jules-feiffer-dead" target="_blank"&gt;has died at 95&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/859721331/suzanne-nuyen"target="_blank"   &gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Suzanne Nuyen&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
