      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.npr.org/2025/01/20/g-s1-43670/up-first-newsletter-donald-trump-inauguration-day-martin-luther-king-jr-day-tiktok</guid>
      <pubDate>Mon, 20 Jan 2025 13:08:04 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div id="storytext" class="storytext storylocation linkLocation"&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Good morning. You're reading the Up First newsletter. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/newsletter/news" target="_blank"&gt;Subscribe&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; here to get it delivered to your inbox, and &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/podcasts/510318/up-first/" target="_blank"&gt;listen&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; to the Up First podcast for all the news you need to start your day.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Today's top stories&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;President-elect Donald Trump will be sworn in today for his second term in the White House.&lt;/strong&gt; He &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/01/19/g-s1-43635/trump-rally-capital-one-preview" target="_blank"&gt;promised quite a show&lt;/a&gt; for his first day in office last night at an hours-long rally at Capitol One Arena in Washington, D.C. His inauguration, originally scheduled outdoors, has been moved to the U.S. Capitol Rotunda due to below-freezing temperatures. His supporters can see him via livestream. Here's &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/01/20/g-s1-43577/donald-trump-inauguration-day-how-to-watch" target="_blank"&gt;how to watch the inauguration festivities&lt;/a&gt; — and what to look out for.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-43639" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 8256;         --source-height: 4644;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8256x4644+0+104/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2F54%2Ffa85f8c048a589a1f967477d54fc%2Fgettyimages-2194234351.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8256x4644+0+104/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2F54%2Ffa85f8c048a589a1f967477d54fc%2Fgettyimages-2194234351.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8256x4644+0+104/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2F54%2Ffa85f8c048a589a1f967477d54fc%2Fgettyimages-2194234351.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8256x4644+0+104/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2F54%2Ffa85f8c048a589a1f967477d54fc%2Fgettyimages-2194234351.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8256x4644+0+104/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2F54%2Ffa85f8c048a589a1f967477d54fc%2Fgettyimages-2194234351.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8256x4644+0+104/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2F54%2Ffa85f8c048a589a1f967477d54fc%2Fgettyimages-2194234351.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8256x4644+0+104/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2F54%2Ffa85f8c048a589a1f967477d54fc%2Fgettyimages-2194234351.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8256x4644+0+104/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2F54%2Ffa85f8c048a589a1f967477d54fc%2Fgettyimages-2194234351.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8256x4644+0+104/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2F54%2Ffa85f8c048a589a1f967477d54fc%2Fgettyimages-2194234351.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8256x4644+0+104/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2F54%2Ffa85f8c048a589a1f967477d54fc%2Fgettyimages-2194234351.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8256x4644+0+104/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2F54%2Ffa85f8c048a589a1f967477d54fc%2Fgettyimages-2194234351.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8256x4644+0+104/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2F54%2Ffa85f8c048a589a1f967477d54fc%2Fgettyimages-2194234351.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8256x4644+0+104/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2F54%2Ffa85f8c048a589a1f967477d54fc%2Fgettyimages-2194234351.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8256x4644+0+104/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2F54%2Ffa85f8c048a589a1f967477d54fc%2Fgettyimages-2194234351.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8256x4644+0+104/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2F54%2Ffa85f8c048a589a1f967477d54fc%2Fgettyimages-2194234351.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8256x4644+0+104/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2F54%2Ffa85f8c048a589a1f967477d54fc%2Fgettyimages-2194234351.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8256x4644+0+104/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2F54%2Ffa85f8c048a589a1f967477d54fc%2Fgettyimages-2194234351.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8256x4644+0+104/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F22%2F54%2Ffa85f8c048a589a1f967477d54fc%2Fgettyimages-2194234351.jpg" class="img" alt="U.S. President-elect Donald Trump reacts during a MAGA victory rally at Capital One Arena in Washington, DC on Sunday, one day ahead of his inauguration ceremony." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 U.S. President-elect Donald Trump reacts during a MAGA victory rally at Capital One Arena in Washington, DC on Sunday, one day ahead of his inauguration ceremony.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Jim Watson/AFP via Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;🎧 &lt;strong&gt;There is a full day of activities planned, including a midday ceremony that could involve Trump signing executive orders&lt;/strong&gt;, NPR's Danielle Kurtzleben tells &lt;em&gt;Up First&lt;/em&gt;. The move indoors will also make a lot of time today &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=1225803712:1265031668" target="_blank"&gt;feel like a traditional Trump rally&lt;/a&gt;, she adds. At last night's rally, Trump talked about carrying out mass deportations quickly and pardoning people convicted for their actions during the Jan. 6, 2021, riot at the U.S. Capitol.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;➡️ &lt;strong&gt;Here's what&lt;/strong&gt; Trump has &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/01/19/nx-s1-5267074/donald-trump-inauguration-2025-analysis" target="_blank"&gt;promised to focus on&lt;/a&gt; during his presidential term.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Around 90 Palestinian prisoners and detainees were freed from Israeli jails yesterday as part of an exchange &lt;/strong&gt;under the Israel-Hamas ceasefire. The release came hours after three Israeli women who had been &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/01/19/g-s1-43571/ceasefire-goes-into-effect-in-gaza" target="_blank"&gt;held hostage in Gaza for 471 days&lt;/a&gt; were set free by Hamas-led militants. There were emotional reunions with families and celebrations on both sides. The hostage and prisoner release is the first phase of what's being called a temporary ceasefire. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;🎧 &lt;strong&gt;"From the moment the ceasefire did go into effect, almost three hours late, you could feel this collective sigh of relief just blanket the country.&lt;/strong&gt; It was a day of tears, jubilation, embraces," NPR's Hadeel Al-Shalchi, who is in Tel Aviv, says. Inside Gaza, Palestinians blasted music from their homes, cheered and honked their car horns when the ceasefire took effect. The skies in Gaza went &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=1225803712:1265031668" target="_blank"&gt;silent for the first time in months&lt;/a&gt; with no Israeli airstrikes. Over 600 trucks of desperately needed aid entered Gaza, according to the United Nations. Hamas is expected to release four more hostages on Saturday.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;➡️ &lt;strong&gt;See photos&lt;/strong&gt; from the &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/the-picture-show/2025/01/19/g-s1-43590/photos-familiesisrael-hamas-ceasefire-takes-effect" target="_blank"&gt;moment families reunited&lt;/a&gt; when the ceasefire took effect.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;TikTok is back online in the U.S. after going dark for around 14 hours on Saturday night. &lt;/strong&gt;The blackout impacted 170 million American users and was &lt;a href="http://www.npr.org/2025/01/19/nx-s1-5267568/tiktok-back-online" target="_blank"&gt;lifted after Trump promised to issue&lt;/a&gt; an executive order to pause the federal ban once he is sworn in. However, the app isn't quite back to normal yet. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;       &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;🎧 &lt;strong&gt;Legal experts have questioned whether Trump can use an executive order as an end-run around a law Congress already passed&lt;/strong&gt;, NPR's Juliana Kim says. Trump said he wants his administration to have more time to work out a deal. The &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=1225803712:1265031668" target="_blank"&gt;timeline to negotiate the deal is not clear,&lt;/a&gt; but he told NBC News he is considering around 90 days. Since the ban, Apple and Google haven't allowed TikTok back in their app stores. New users cannot download it, and the app can't receive software updates to fix bugs or other issues.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Today's listen&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="res510013863" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 3674;         --source-height: 2066;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2017/01/15/king-speech_wide-28e5beced6f03ff1c47adf9240c8c306ea7b8e0d.jpg?s=400&amp;c=85&amp;f=webp 400w, https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2017/01/15/king-speech_wide-28e5beced6f03ff1c47adf9240c8c306ea7b8e0d.jpg?s=600&amp;c=85&amp;f=webp 600w, https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2017/01/15/king-speech_wide-28e5beced6f03ff1c47adf9240c8c306ea7b8e0d.jpg?s=800&amp;c=85&amp;f=webp 800w, https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2017/01/15/king-speech_wide-28e5beced6f03ff1c47adf9240c8c306ea7b8e0d.jpg?s=900&amp;c=85&amp;f=webp 900w, https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2017/01/15/king-speech_wide-28e5beced6f03ff1c47adf9240c8c306ea7b8e0d.jpg?s=1200&amp;c=85&amp;f=webp 1200w, https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2017/01/15/king-speech_wide-28e5beced6f03ff1c47adf9240c8c306ea7b8e0d.jpg?s=1600&amp;c=85&amp;f=webp 1600w, https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2017/01/15/king-speech_wide-28e5beced6f03ff1c47adf9240c8c306ea7b8e0d.jpg?s=1800&amp;c=85&amp;f=webp 1800w" data-template="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2017/01/15/king-speech_wide-28e5beced6f03ff1c47adf9240c8c306ea7b8e0d.jpg?s={width}&amp;c={quality}&amp;f={format}" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2017/01/15/king-speech_wide-28e5beced6f03ff1c47adf9240c8c306ea7b8e0d.jpg?s=400&amp;c=85&amp;f=jpeg 400w, https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2017/01/15/king-speech_wide-28e5beced6f03ff1c47adf9240c8c306ea7b8e0d.jpg?s=600&amp;c=85&amp;f=jpeg 600w, https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2017/01/15/king-speech_wide-28e5beced6f03ff1c47adf9240c8c306ea7b8e0d.jpg?s=800&amp;c=85&amp;f=jpeg 800w, https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2017/01/15/king-speech_wide-28e5beced6f03ff1c47adf9240c8c306ea7b8e0d.jpg?s=900&amp;c=85&amp;f=jpeg 900w, https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2017/01/15/king-speech_wide-28e5beced6f03ff1c47adf9240c8c306ea7b8e0d.jpg?s=1200&amp;c=85&amp;f=jpeg 1200w, https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2017/01/15/king-speech_wide-28e5beced6f03ff1c47adf9240c8c306ea7b8e0d.jpg?s=1600&amp;c=85&amp;f=jpeg 1600w, https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2017/01/15/king-speech_wide-28e5beced6f03ff1c47adf9240c8c306ea7b8e0d.jpg?s=1800&amp;c=85&amp;f=jpeg 1800w" data-template="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2017/01/15/king-speech_wide-28e5beced6f03ff1c47adf9240c8c306ea7b8e0d.jpg?s={width}&amp;c={quality}&amp;f={format}" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2017/01/15/king-speech_wide-28e5beced6f03ff1c47adf9240c8c306ea7b8e0d.jpg?s=1100&amp;c=50&amp;f=jpeg" data-template="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2017/01/15/king-speech_wide-28e5beced6f03ff1c47adf9240c8c306ea7b8e0d.jpg?s={width}&amp;c={quality}&amp;f={format}" class="img" alt="Civil rights leader Martin Luther King Jr. addresses the crowd at the Lincoln Memorial in Washington, D.C., where he gave his &amp;quot;I Have a Dream&amp;quot; speech on Aug. 28, 1963, as part of the March on Washington." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt;          &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Civil rights leader Martin Luther King Jr. addresses the crowd at the Lincoln Memorial in Washington, D.C., where he gave his "I Have a Dream" speech on Aug. 28, 1963, as part of the March on Washington.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          AFP via Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;      &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Martin Luther King Jr. has a lasting legacy and even pulled some focus during the 1960 presidential election.&lt;/strong&gt; Atlanta activist Lonnie C. King noticed something was missing from Vice President Richard Nixon and Sen. John F. Kennedy's presidential campaigns. There was no mention of the unrest happening in the South. Lonnie devised a plan to bring awareness, enlisting the help of his childhood friend, MLK Jr. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;🎧 &lt;strong&gt;Listen to Lonnie describe his plan&lt;/strong&gt;, how it worked and &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=nx-s1-5262376:nx-s1-5327157-1" target="_blank"&gt;how it impacted the presidential election&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Life advice&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-43328" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 3000;         --source-height: 1688;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+157/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F69%2Fe4%2F28d5112b4b9ba6446b2f8e66e050%2Flk-yougottaeat.png 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+157/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F69%2Fe4%2F28d5112b4b9ba6446b2f8e66e050%2Flk-yougottaeat.png 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+157/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F69%2Fe4%2F28d5112b4b9ba6446b2f8e66e050%2Flk-yougottaeat.png 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+157/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F69%2Fe4%2F28d5112b4b9ba6446b2f8e66e050%2Flk-yougottaeat.png 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+157/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F69%2Fe4%2F28d5112b4b9ba6446b2f8e66e050%2Flk-yougottaeat.png 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+157/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F69%2Fe4%2F28d5112b4b9ba6446b2f8e66e050%2Flk-yougottaeat.png 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+157/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F69%2Fe4%2F28d5112b4b9ba6446b2f8e66e050%2Flk-yougottaeat.png 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+157/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F69%2Fe4%2F28d5112b4b9ba6446b2f8e66e050%2Flk-yougottaeat.png" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+157/resize/400/quality/85/format/png/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F69%2Fe4%2F28d5112b4b9ba6446b2f8e66e050%2Flk-yougottaeat.png 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+157/resize/600/quality/85/format/png/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F69%2Fe4%2F28d5112b4b9ba6446b2f8e66e050%2Flk-yougottaeat.png 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+157/resize/800/quality/85/format/png/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F69%2Fe4%2F28d5112b4b9ba6446b2f8e66e050%2Flk-yougottaeat.png 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+157/resize/900/quality/85/format/png/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F69%2Fe4%2F28d5112b4b9ba6446b2f8e66e050%2Flk-yougottaeat.png 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+157/resize/1200/quality/85/format/png/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F69%2Fe4%2F28d5112b4b9ba6446b2f8e66e050%2Flk-yougottaeat.png 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+157/resize/1600/quality/85/format/png/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F69%2Fe4%2F28d5112b4b9ba6446b2f8e66e050%2Flk-yougottaeat.png 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+157/resize/1800/quality/85/format/png/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F69%2Fe4%2F28d5112b4b9ba6446b2f8e66e050%2Flk-yougottaeat.png 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+157/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F69%2Fe4%2F28d5112b4b9ba6446b2f8e66e050%2Flk-yougottaeat.png" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/png" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+157/resize/1100/quality/50/format/png/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F69%2Fe4%2F28d5112b4b9ba6446b2f8e66e050%2Flk-yougottaeat.png" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+157/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F69%2Fe4%2F28d5112b4b9ba6446b2f8e66e050%2Flk-yougottaeat.png" class="img" alt="Periwinkle-colored line drawings of meal ideas and toppings, including from left to right, clockwise: a cheese board, seasoning like salt, pepper, and peanut butter, instant ramen, cottage cheese with nuts, an omelet, and bags of frozen veggies and cheese. " loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Even if you dislike cooking, you still have to eat every day. Margaret Eby, author of &lt;em&gt;You Gotta Eat: Real-Life Strategies for Feeding Yourself When Cooking Feels Impossible&lt;/em&gt;, shares practical tips for getting meals on the table, including counting assembling as cooking, expanding your idea of what counts as dinner and dressing up easy foods like cottage cheese or instant ramen with simple, nutritious toppings.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Illustrations by Mariá Toro, excerpted from &lt;i&gt;You Gotta Eat&lt;/i&gt; by Margaret Eby (Quirk Books, 2024)                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cooking seems simple in theory, but it can feel like a chore to some. &lt;/strong&gt;But there is a way to flip that feeling around. Margaret Eby, author of &lt;em&gt;You Gotta Eat: Real Life Strategies for Feeding Yourself When Cooking Feels Impossible&lt;/em&gt;, says you have to change how you think of what it means to prepare food. Here's how to &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/01/18/nx-s1-5226105/hate-cooking-3-mindsets-to-make-it-less-of-a-chore" target="_blank"&gt;gain more confidence in the kitchen&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;🍳 &lt;strong&gt;Assembling food counts as cooking. &lt;/strong&gt;Throw a few ingredients in a slow cooker or make a sandwich.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;🍳 &lt;strong&gt;Think outside the box for dinner. &lt;/strong&gt;A charcuterie board isn't a typical dinner idea, but why not try it? You can include arranged cheese, cured meats and more on your platter.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;🍳 &lt;strong&gt;Don't let recipes control you. &lt;/strong&gt;Remember, you don't need all the ingredients; play around with things you might or might not want to eat.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Read more about changing your mindset around cooking, plus get a recipe&lt;/strong&gt; to make a bean salad &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/01/18/nx-s1-5226105/hate-cooking-3-mindsets-to-make-it-less-of-a-chore" target="_blank"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;3 things to know before you go&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-43627" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 4176;         --source-height: 2349;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4176x2349+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0b%2F50%2F58538bd94e17b75ec02343972740%2Fgettyimages-1485531759.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4176x2349+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0b%2F50%2F58538bd94e17b75ec02343972740%2Fgettyimages-1485531759.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4176x2349+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0b%2F50%2F58538bd94e17b75ec02343972740%2Fgettyimages-1485531759.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4176x2349+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0b%2F50%2F58538bd94e17b75ec02343972740%2Fgettyimages-1485531759.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4176x2349+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0b%2F50%2F58538bd94e17b75ec02343972740%2Fgettyimages-1485531759.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4176x2349+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0b%2F50%2F58538bd94e17b75ec02343972740%2Fgettyimages-1485531759.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4176x2349+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0b%2F50%2F58538bd94e17b75ec02343972740%2Fgettyimages-1485531759.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4176x2349+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0b%2F50%2F58538bd94e17b75ec02343972740%2Fgettyimages-1485531759.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4176x2349+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0b%2F50%2F58538bd94e17b75ec02343972740%2Fgettyimages-1485531759.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4176x2349+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0b%2F50%2F58538bd94e17b75ec02343972740%2Fgettyimages-1485531759.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4176x2349+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0b%2F50%2F58538bd94e17b75ec02343972740%2Fgettyimages-1485531759.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4176x2349+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0b%2F50%2F58538bd94e17b75ec02343972740%2Fgettyimages-1485531759.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4176x2349+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0b%2F50%2F58538bd94e17b75ec02343972740%2Fgettyimages-1485531759.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4176x2349+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0b%2F50%2F58538bd94e17b75ec02343972740%2Fgettyimages-1485531759.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4176x2349+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0b%2F50%2F58538bd94e17b75ec02343972740%2Fgettyimages-1485531759.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4176x2349+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0b%2F50%2F58538bd94e17b75ec02343972740%2Fgettyimages-1485531759.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4176x2349+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0b%2F50%2F58538bd94e17b75ec02343972740%2Fgettyimages-1485531759.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4176x2349+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0b%2F50%2F58538bd94e17b75ec02343972740%2Fgettyimages-1485531759.jpg" class="img" alt="Byron Allen speaks at the Allen Media Group upfront presentation at Avra on April 26, 2023 in New York City." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Byron Allen speaks at the Allen Media Group upfront presentation at Avra on April 26, 2023 in New York City.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Chance Yeh/Getty Images for Allen Media Group/The Weather Channel                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Meteorologists at 27 local TV news stations could face layoffs after Allen Media Group announced a new local weather initiative with The Weather Channel.&lt;/strong&gt; The group said the new format will have "&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/01/19/nx-s1-5267507/local-tv-meteorologists-the-weather-channel-layoffs" target="_blank"&gt;additional visual storytelling capabilities&lt;/a&gt;" across its stations.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The U.S. Department of Health and Human Services announced it will award Moderna $590 million to accelerate &lt;/strong&gt;the development of influenza vaccines, &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/01/18/nx-s1-5266868/bird-flu-vaccine-moderna" target="_blank"&gt;including those for bird flu&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Famed novelist and essayist Virginia Woolf has also been revealed to be a poet&lt;/strong&gt;, according to &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/01/17/nx-s1-5260964/virginia-woolf-poems-niece-nephew" target="_blank"&gt;documents uncovered at the Harry Ransom Center&lt;/a&gt;, an archive library at the University of Texas at Austin.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/859721331/suzanne-nuyen"target="_blank"   &gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Suzanne Nuyen&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
