="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1100x619+0+57/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fba%2F04%2Ffc7dd43a479dbf746c9b7c5f1f97%2Fnpr-brightspotcdn-1.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1100x619+0+57/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fba%2F04%2Ffc7dd43a479dbf746c9b7c5f1f97%2Fnpr-brightspotcdn-1.jpg" class="img" alt="President Biden speaks during a White House event in this Jan. 5, 2025 file photo." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 President Biden speaks during a White House event in this Jan. 5, 2025 file photo.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Kent Nishimura/Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;President Biden announced that he is commuting the sentences of nearly 2,500 people convicted of non-violent drug crimes&lt;/strong&gt;, who are serving &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/01/17/g-s1-41788/biden-pardons-commutations-drug-sentences" target="_blank"&gt;significantly longer sentences than they would&lt;/a&gt; receive today.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hino Motors, a Toyota subsidiary that produces commercial trucks, has pleaded guilty to submitting false emissions data&lt;/strong&gt; to regulators for more than 100,000 heavy-duty trucks. The company will pay &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/01/16/nx-s1-5262576/hino-toyota-trucks-emissions-fraud" target="_blank"&gt;$1.6 billion in fines and penalties&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Conan O'Brien will receive the Mark Twain Prize for American Humor&lt;/strong&gt; in March. &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/01/16/nx-s1-5261026/conan-obrien-mark-twain-prize" target="_blank"&gt;Past recipients of this award&lt;/a&gt; include Richard Pryor, George Carlin, Lily Tomlin, Whoopi Goldberg and Kevin Hart.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/859721331/suzanne-nuyen"target="_blank"   &gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Suzanne Nuyen&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
